Create Laravel project
Start a fresh Laravel 10 project using Composer.
composer create-project laravel/laravel MedClinicSystem
cd MedClinicSystem

2
Install Laravel Breeze
Breeze scaffolds login, register, password reset, and email verify.
composer require laravel/breeze --dev

3
Scaffold Breeze with Blade
Use the Blade stack (plain PHP, no React/Vue needed).
php artisan breeze:install blade

4
Install Node & compile assets
Installs Tailwind CSS and compiles the frontend.
npm install
npm run build

5
Configure .env database
Set your MySQL credentials in the .env file.
DB_DATABASE=medclinic_db
DB_USERNAME=root
DB_PASSWORD=your_password

6
Run migrations
Creates the users, sessions, and password_reset_tokens tables.
php artisan migrate

7
Add role column to users
Generate a migration to add role and is_active fields.
php artisan make:migration add_role_to_users_table

8
Edit the migration file
Inside the generated migration's up() method, add:
$table->enum('role', ['admin','staff'])
      ->default('staff')->after('email');
$table->boolean('is_active')
      ->default(true)->after('role');

9
Migrate again
Applies the new role and is_active columns to users table.
php artisan migrate

10
Update User model fillable
Open app/Models/User.php and add the new fields.
protected $fillable = [
  'name','email','password',
  'role','is_active',
];

11
Seed an admin user
Create a seeder so you can log in right away.
php artisan make:seeder UserSeeder
php artisan db:seed --class=UserSeeder

12
Customise the login view
Edit the Breeze-generated file to match your clinic's branding.
resources/views/auth/login.blade.php

13
Customise the register view
Add role selector and any extra fields your clinic needs.
resources/views/auth/register.blade.php

14
Block inactive accounts on login
Add this check inside AuthenticatedSessionController@store, right after authenticate():
if (!auth()->user()->is_active) {
  auth()->logout();
  return back()->withErrors([
    'email'=>'Account deactivated.'
  ]);

}
15
Start the dev server
Visit http://localhost:8000/login to see the live form.
php artisan serve

